[
    {
        "id": "flow1",
        "type": "tab",
        "label": "Overcharge Protection",
        "disabled": false,
        "info": "# Battery Overcharge Protection\n\nThis flow monitors voltage and activates an electronic load when voltage exceeds 5V to prevent overcharging.\n\n## Components:\n- **Automation**: Controllable 1-second timer\n- **DMM**: Reads voltage from dmm-1\n- **Threshold**: Checks if voltage > 5V\n- **ELL**: Controls electronic load (ON when high, OFF when safe)\n\n## How to Use:\n1. Import this flow\n2. Deploy\n3. Click the automation node button to start/stop\n4. Monitor from BenchMesh UI\n\n## Safety:\n- Green light on automation = protection active\n- Red light = protection stopped (manual intervention needed)"
    },
    {
        "id": "automation_node",
        "type": "benchmesh-automation",
        "z": "flow1",
        "name": "Battery Protection Timer",
        "automationName": "Overcharge Protection",
        "frequency": 1000,
        "enabled": false,
        "x": 180,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": [
            [
                "dmm_read"
            ]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "dmm_read",
        "type": "benchmesh-dmm",
        "z": "flow1",
        "name": "Read Battery Voltage",
        "deviceId": "dmm-1",
        "channel": "1",
        "operation": "query_measurement",
        "apiBase": "http://localhost:57666",
        "x": 420,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": [
            [
                "threshold_check",
                "debug_voltage"
            ]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "threshold_check",
        "type": "benchmesh-threshold",
        "z": "flow1",
        "name": "Voltage > 5V?",
        "threshold": 5,
        "comparison": "gt",
        "property": "value",
        "x": 660,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": [
